                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3s46hs3r/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>up my mind to defer my journey, though I thereby will in all probabili<lb/>ty lose\n                the fine weather which we now have. Next <date>Sunday</date><lb/> I have <add>יאהר\n                    צייט</add> for my father and on <date>Tuesday</date> I believe they will<lb/>\n                set a tombstone for <persName>Mr Allen</persName>, when his year expires; so I\n                shall<lb/> not get off next week either. So you see, Uncle, that my little<lb/>\n                excursion depend upon so many circumstances, that I can not even<lb/> leave within\n                the week if I feel ever so much inclined to travel.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Have any Baltimorean signed the prospectus for the Occident?<lb/> I\n                have about 60 already in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and vicinity, and\n                expect at<lb/> least 20 more; how many there are in <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                I shall learn only<lb/> when I get there; as the people there are too busy to\n                write.<lb/> I myself would never have thought of a paper for the present;<lb/> but I\n                have been induced to give the proposal in consequence<lb/> of solicitation from\n                various quarters. Whether the very persons who<lb/> urged me will do any thing\n                appears very doubtful; but there is <add>?</add><lb/> consolation if I do not print\n                the paper I shall lose nothing by <add>?</add></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">All your friends desire to be remembered; <persName>Amelia\n                    Allen</persName> in particu<lb/>lar told me I must mention her name. It is\n                hardly requisite to<lb/> write a page full of names; so I leave you to judge who\n                all<lb/> enquire about you. Give my love to <persName>Aunt R.</persName>\n                <persName>Rachel</persName>, <persName>Mr Judah</persName><lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs Block</persName>, the <persName>Ettings</persName>, and all\n                our mutual friends.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">With high regard</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">your obt. Nephew</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Isaac Leeser</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>I had last week a letter</p>\n            <p>from <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName> of <placeName>Jamaica</placeName></p>\n            <p>neither he nor his wife was well at</p>\n            <p>the time. He makes an apology for</p>\n            <p>not sending <add>אתרוגים</add>.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3s46hs3r/canvas/p3"
                }
